theorem Topology.P3_and_isClosed_implies_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hClosed : IsClosed A) (hP3 : Topology.P3 A) :
    IsOpen A := by
  have h₁ : A ⊆ interior A := by
    intro x hx
    have : x ∈ interior (closure A) := hP3 hx
    simpa [hClosed.closure_eq] using this
  have h_eq : (A : Set X) = interior A :=
    Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ interior_subset
  simpa [h_eq] using (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior A))

theorem Topology.P3_iff_exists_open_between {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 A ↔ ∃ U : Set X, IsOpen U ∧ A ⊆ U ∧ U ⊆ closure A := by
  constructor
  · intro hA
    refine ⟨interior (closure A), isOpen_interior, hA, interior_subset⟩
  · rintro ⟨U, hUopen, hAU, hUcl⟩
    dsimp [Topology.P3]
    have hUsubset : U ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_maximal hUcl hUopen
    exact Set.Subset.trans hAU hUsubset
